                    <span>Don't get me wrong!! It's a great book, for understanding COM+ and use it, without all the headache of learning "why".<BR>But i think many people would believe is a good about .NET and how to use COM Services, but you will get only a few pages about implementing both technologies together.<BR>But, like i've said, it's a good book about COM Services.</span>
                  
